When `!hasNext()` is true and `offset === 0`, the original returns `[]`, but the mutated code falls through to `else if (this.offset === 0)` which returns `this.ops.slice(this.index)`.

When the iterator is exhausted (`index >= ops.length`), `this.offset` is 0, so the mutated code would execute `this.ops.slice(this.index)` which returns `[]` too - same result!

I need a case where `!hasNext()` is true but `offset !== 0`. Actually `hasNext()` returns false only when `peekLength()` returns `Infinity`, which only happens when `this.ops[this.index]` is falsy. In that case `offset` would be 0...

